<script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What drives property values in Burbank?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Burbank property values are driven primarily by land size, useable land character, the position of the holding relative to Bulimba Creek and the surrounding bushland reserves, and the quality and configuration of any equestrian or hobby-farm infrastructure on the block. A correctly positioned acreage holding with cleared useable land, mains-power services and quality fencing sits in a different value tier to a smaller or partially encumbered block." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take to sell a home in Burbank?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Well-presented Burbank acreage properties typically sell within 40 to 70 days. The buyer pool is smaller and more specific than a standard residential suburb, and a campaign needs the time to reach lifestyle buyers from across south-east Queensland. Correct pricing against recent acreage comparables, not standard residential comparables, is the most reliable predictor of campaign length." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the lifestyle like in Burbank?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Burbank offers a semi-rural lifestyle within Brisbane city limits, with bushland reserves along Bulimba Creek, equestrian and hobby-farm character on the larger acreage blocks, and quick road access to Carindale, Mount Gravatt and the Gateway Motorway. It appeals to households who want space, privacy and the ability to keep horses or run a small holding while staying inside the Brisbane City Council area." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Burbank a good suburb to buy in right now?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Burbank's tightly held acreage character and proximity to Carindale and the eastern suburbs has supported steady demand from lifestyle buyers through the recent cycle. Useable acreage inside the Brisbane City Council boundary is a scarce asset, and properties that combine quality infrastructure with a sound block continue to attract committed buyers from across south-east Queensland." }
    }
  ]
})}</script>

