<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Tightly held acreage on Brisbane's eastern fringe.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Burbank is one of the tightest acreage suburbs inside the Brisbane City Council boundary, defined by larger lifestyle holdings, the Bulimba Creek bushland reserves, and an established equestrian and hobby-farm character. The suburb sits just behind Chandler and Mackenzie, with easy road access into Carindale, Mount Gravatt and onto the Gateway Motorway. It attracts lifestyle buyers who want genuine acreage privacy while staying inside the Brisbane local government area.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
<div style="background:#fff; border-left:4px solid #b98229; padding:2rem 2rem 1.75rem; margin:2rem 0; border-radius:16px;">
