</style>
<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know Burbank well. I understand the lifestyle buyer profile, what makes one acreage holding outperform another, and how to position a property to reach the specific south-east Queensland audience that buys here.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Burbank's character is set by useable land. The blocks that combine cleared paddocks with quality fencing, mains-power services, established stables or sheds and a sound home consistently command the strongest results. The bushland reserves along Bulimba Creek shape the western and southern edges of the suburb, and properties that adjoin or look into the reserves carry a privacy and outlook premium. The internal hierarchy of streets, blocks and infrastructure standards inside Burbank is wider than the price ranges from outside the suburb suggest, and campaign positioning needs to reflect that variation.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
